12 O&#039;CLOCK HIGH 

210. Grant Me No Favor   11/15/1965 
On a bombing mission into Norway, Lieutenant Col. Christy aborts the mission after 10 out his 21 planes get shot down. When he returns, Gallagher sends an angry note to newly promoted Major General Britt asking why the target is secret, "How can his men keep risking there lives for a secret target". Summoned by Britt to what turns out to be Britt&#039;s promotion party, he is surprised to see his father Lieutenant General Max Gallagher. General Gallagher intercedes with General Pritchard to keep Pritchard from seeing and disciplining Colonel Gallagher.
  Guest star: Robert Dornan (Gallagher&#039;s Co-Pilot) , Rich Falk (Christy&#039;s co-pilot), Robert Hathaway (Wounded N.C.O.), Mike Doherty (M.P. Officer), Barry Sullivan (Lieutenant General Gallagher), Frank Aletter (Lieutenant Colonel Christy), JacQueline Russell (WAC Captain), Kirby Brumfield (Aide)

211. Storm at Twilight   11/22/1965  
Harv and Lieutenant Colonel Rogers, the 918ths acting commander, watch the latest mission come back very chewed up and missing at least 6 six planes. Harvey feels responsible. Sandy hands him a telegram, his son isMIA. Harvey goes to see General Britt and requests to go back on flying status. He gets an age waiver. Gallagher comes back and is furious with Harvey. He passes his physical by memorizing the eye chart. Gallagher puts Harvey through the wringer but Harvey passes his flight test. On the mission to bomb the marshalling yards at Antwerp, they make the run then get attacked by ME-109&#039;s.
Guest star: James Devine (Navigator), Bruce Glover (Waist Gunner), Ray McGrath (Young Lieutenant), Ted Knight (Lieutenant Colonel Rogers)
